(74, 'Co-lend', '/platformLogo/Co-lend.png', '[\"United Kingdom\"]', '[\"Equity\"]', '[\"Real estate\"]', '2019', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://www.co-lend.co.uk/', '1,000 GBP', 'N/A', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Co-lend is a crowdfunding platform based in the United Kingdom that focuses on equity investment in the real estate industry. Established in 2019, Co-lend offers an opportunity for investors to connect with professional landlords and participate in asset-backed investment projects.\n\nWith a minimum investment requirement of 1,000 GBP, Co-lend caters to a wide range of investors, allowing both individuals and institutions to get involved. The platform aims to democratize the real estate market by providing access to investment opportunities that were previously reserved for large financial institutions.\n\nAs an equity crowdfunding platform, Co-lend enables investors to become partial owners of real estate properties. By pooling funds from multiple investors, Co-lend allows individuals to diversify their investment portfolio and potentially earn returns from the property\'s performance.\n\nOne notable aspect of Co-lend is the absence of an advertised return. While the exact potential returns are not specified on the platform, Co-lend focuses on providing exciting investment opportunities that are backed by tangible assets. This can provide investors with confidence in the security of their investments.\n\nCo-lend\'s website offers a user-friendly interface where investors can browse and select investment projects that align with their preferences and financial goals. Although information about available languages is not provided, the platform caters to investors in the United Kingdom.\n\nOverall, Co-lend aims to bridge the gap between investors and professional landlords, offering an avenue for individuals and institutions alike to participate in the UK real estate market and potentially earn returns through equity investments.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL,