(109, 'EthicHub', '/platformLogo/EthicHub.png', '[\"Spain\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"Farming\"]', '2017', 'N/A', '[\"English\",\"Spanish\"]', NULL, 'https://app.ethichub.com/', '20 EUR', 'N/A', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'EthicHub is a crowdfunding platform based in Spain that specializes in P2P lending for the farming industry. Founded in 2017, EthicHub aims to connect unbanked small farmers with lenders and coffee buyers worldwide, forming a beneficial ecosystem for all parties involved. \n\nOne of the key features of EthicHub is its ability to facilitate loans between lenders and small farmers who otherwise may not have access to traditional banking services. By connecting these farmers with lenders, EthicHub helps to bridge the gap and provide crucial financial support for agricultural projects.\n\nEthicHub operates as a marketplace, linking lenders and borrowers in a P2P lending model. This allows individuals and corporations to invest in the farming industry, providing necessary funds for agricultural activities. The platform embraces the idea of crowdfunding, enabling people from all over the world to support small farmers and invest in sustainable agriculture.\n\nEthicHub supports multiple languages, including English and Spanish, catering to a diverse user base. The minimum investment required to participate on the platform is 20 EUR, making it accessible to a wide range of investors.\n\nAlthough the specific return on investment is not advertised, users can expect financial and social returns by investing in EthicHub. The platform aims to create a win-win situation for both lenders and farmers, fostering sustainable and inclusive agricultural practices.\n\nOverall, EthicHub provides an innovative and inclusive platform for individuals and corporations to invest in the farming industry, supporting small and unbanked farmers globally.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Personal, Corporate', 'ethichub', '2023-08-08 09:32:55', '2023-08-08 09:32:55'),
