(140, 'Sourced Capital', '/platformLogo/Sourced Capital.png', '[\"United Kingdom\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"Real estate\"]', '2017', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://sourcedcapital.co/', '250 GBP', 'N/A', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Sourced Capital is a crowdfunding platform based in the United Kingdom that specializes in P2P lending in the real estate industry. It was founded in 2017 and aims to provide investors with the opportunity to generate impressive returns by investing their savings, ISAs, and pensions into loans that are secured against properties in the UK.\n\nThe platform offers an avenue for individuals to invest in real estate without having to directly purchase properties themselves. By pooling their investments together, investors can collectively finance property projects and earn returns on their investments.\n\nSourced Capital operates exclusively in the United Kingdom and offers a minimum investment of £250. While the advertised return is not specified, investors can expect to earn returns based on the performance of the property loans they invest in.\n\nThe platform provides an accessible and user-friendly website (https://sourcedcapital.co/) for potential investors to explore and learn more about the investment opportunities available. It also offers transparency by providing extensive information on the properties and loans available for investment.\n\nSourced Capital is open to anyone who wishes to invest, regardless of their professional or financial status. Whether individuals are looking to diversify their investment portfolio, save for their retirement, or generate passive income, Sourced Capital offers an attractive opportunity to invest in the UK real estate market.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 'sourcedcapital', '2023-08-08 09:32:55', '2023-08-08 09:32:55'),
(141, 'Lendora', '/platformLogo/Lendora.png', '[\"Switzerland\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"SME\"]', '2016', 'CHE 342.591.844', '[\"English\",\"French\",\"Dutch\"]', NULL, 'https://lendora.ch/', '1 EUR', 'N/A', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Lendora is a Swiss crowdlending startup that operates as a peer-to-peer lending platform. Established in 2016, Lendora aims to make credit more accessible for borrowers and investing more rewarding for investors by connecting them through their online platform. The platform primarily focuses on facilitating loans for small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) within Switzerland.\n\nCurrently, Lendora has managed to gather a community of over 1,500 investors, which they refer to as \"smart-money investors\". These investors have the opportunity to finance loan requests published on the platform, with a minimum investment amount of just 1 EUR. However, the advertised return on investment is not disclosed.\n\nIn order to comply with the regulations of the Anti-Money Laundering Act (AMLA), Lendora is required to formally identify all investors who sign up on their platform. As a result, only individuals who possess a registered bank account in Switzerland are allowed to participate in financing the loan requests. It is important to note that credit professionals are excluded from participating in investments through Lendora.\n\nLendora\'s website provides information in multiple languages, including English, French, and Dutch, to cater to a wider audience. With their user-friendly interface and emphasis on connecting borrowers and investors, Lendora aims to revolutionize the lending industry in Switzerland.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Anyone who owns a registered bank account in Switzerland can participate in financing the loan requests published on Lendora, as long as he or she is not a credit professional. As a registered financial intermediary and in accordance with the Anti-Money Laundering Act (AMLA), Lendora must formally identify all investors who sign up on the platform.', 'lendora', '2023-08-08 09:32:55', '2023-08-08 09:32:55'),
