(238, 'Lenndy', '/platformLogo/Lenndy.png', '[\"Lithuania\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"SME\"]', '2015', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://lenndy.com/', '10 EUR', 'N/A', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Lenndy is a crowdfunding platform based in Lithuania that specializes in peer-to-peer (P2P) lending. It was founded in 2015 and primarily caters to Small and Medium Enterprises (SMEs) in need of funding. The platform allows investors to invest in loans by purchasing existing loan rights. Through Lenndy, non-banking loan administrators have the option to transfer the rights of previously issued loans.\n\nLenndy utilizes advanced technological solutions to make the lending process smooth and efficient for both borrowers and investors. The platform aims to connect borrowers in need of funds with individuals looking to invest their money. By buying out prior issued loan rights, investors can earn potential returns on their investments.\n\nLenndy\'s website, available at https://lenndy.com/, provides information about the platform and allows users to sign up and start investing. The minimum investment required to participate is 10 EUR. However, the advertised return on investment is not specified, so investors would need to evaluate the potential returns on a case-by-case basis.\n\nOverall, Lenndy offers a convenient and user-friendly platform for P2P lending, enabling investors to support SMEs in Lithuania and potentially earn returns on their investments.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 'lenndy', '2023-08-08 09:32:55', '2023-08-08 09:32:55'),
(239, 'Credimi', '/platformLogo/Credimi.png', '[\"Italy\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"SME\"]', '2015', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://www.credimi.com/', '1 EUR', 'N/A', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Credimi is a crowdfunding platform based in Italy that specializes in P2P lending for small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs). Founded in 2015, it is the largest digital lender for Italian SMEs and has quickly established itself as a leading fintech company in digital financing for companies in Continental Europe. Credimi operates as a financial intermediary authorized and supervised by the Bank of Italy.\n\nThe platform aims to make access to credit easier for SMEs, providing them with the necessary funds to grow and expand their businesses. It offers an online marketplace where individuals can invest in these SMEs by lending them money. The minimum investment on Credimi is only 1 EUR, making it accessible to a wide range of potential investors.\n\nUnlike other crowdfunding platforms, Credimi does not advertise a specific return on investment. This means that investors\' returns may vary depending on the performance of the SMEs they have invested in.\n\nCredimi\'s website provides information about the platform and its services. Unfortunately, no information is provided about the languages ​​supported on the platform. However, it can be assumed that Italian is supported since Credimi primarily caters to Italian SMEs.\n\nIn summary, Credimi is an Italian crowdfunding platform that focuses on P2P lending for SMEs. It offers individuals the opportunity to invest in these SMEs with a minimum investment of 1 EUR. As a regulated financial intermediary, Credimi aims to make access to credit easier for small and medium-sized businesses in Italy.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 'credimi', '2023-08-08 09:32:55', '2023-08-08 09:32:55'),
