(262, 'Fundovino', '/platformLogo/Fundovino.png', '[\"France\"]', '[\"Equity\"]', '[\"Farming\"]', '2014', '18000564', '[\"French\",\"English\"]', NULL, 'https://www.fundovino.com/fr', '30€', 'N/A', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Fundovino is a crowdfunding platform based in France that focuses on equity investments in the farming industry, specifically in the field of wine production. The platform was founded in 2014 and is available in both French and English languages. The minimum investment required on Fundovino is 30 and the platform does not advertise a specific return on investment.\n\nFundovino is a collaborative project led by partners with backgrounds in hotel and catering, banking, digital, and wine trade. Each partner contributes their expertise in areas such as management, development, marketing, and communication. The platform aims to provide access to a diverse range of wines that have been approved by a tasting committee consisting of industry professionals.\n\nFundovino prioritizes wines that meet various taste requirements, regardless of the labeling or certification methods used by the winemakers. They emphasize the importance of environmentally friendly cultivation and vinification practices, advocating for organic, Demeter, biodyvin, HVE, and natural wines.\n\nA key objective of Fundovino is to support and promote artisanal and family viticulture. This includes enabling winegrowers to acquire their own vineyards whenever possible. By participating in the Fundovino investment model, individuals can contribute to the preservation and growth of sustainable and quality-focused wine production in France. For more information, individuals can visit the Fundovino website at https://www.fundovino.com/fr.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A “fundovino” is a wine investment, which pursues several goals: – to provide access to a lease made up of wines with taste qualities validated by our tasting committee, made up of recognized professionals in the sector. -we are