(385, 'Assetz Capital', '/platformLogo/Assetz Capital.png', '[\"United Kingdom\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"SME\"]', '2012', '724996', '[\"English\"]', NULL, 'https://www.assetzcapital.co.uk/', '1 GBP', 'Up to 4%', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Any individual or business can invest through Assetz Capital as long as they meet certain criteria. The platform focuses on P2P lending, meaning that borrowers and lenders are connected directly through the platform. Assetz Capital aims to provide alternative funding sources to both SMEs and property developers in the United Kingdom.\n\nEstablished in 2012, Assetz Capital has quickly become one of the fastest-growing peer-to-peer lenders in the UK. The platform offers a range of investment opportunities, allowing investors to diversify their portfolio and earn attractive returns.\n\nInvestors can easily sign up through the website, which is available in English. The minimum investment amount is only 1 GBP, making it accessible to a wide range of investors. Assetz Capital advertises a return of up to 4% on investments, presenting an attractive opportunity for those looking to grow their money.\n\nOverall, Assetz Capital provides a user-friendly and accessible crowdfunding platform for individuals and businesses in the UK. With its focus on P2P lending and alternative funding sources, the platform offers a unique opportunity to support and invest in SMEs and property developers while earning competitive returns.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL, 'assetzcapital', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(386, 'Tudigo', '/platformLogo/Tudigo.png', '[\"France\"]', '[\"Donation\"]', '[\"SME\"]', '2012', '14002504', '[\"French\"]', NULL, 'https://www.tudigo.co/', '100 EUR', 'N/A', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Tudigo is a crowdfunding platform founded in 2012 and based in France. It operates as a donation-based crowdfunding platform, allowing individuals and communities to financially support small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) in their towns or neighborhoods. The platform aims to empower communities to back up local businesses by sponsoring their projects.\n\nTudigo\'s website, available in French, serves as a hub for connecting businesses with potential funders who are interested in supporting local ventures. The platform encourages individuals to make a minimum investment of 100 EUR or more to contribute to the success of these businesses.\n\nAs a donation-based crowdfunding platform, Tudigo focuses on supporting SMEs and does not offer an advertised return on investment. Instead, the funders of a particular project may receive exclusive benefits or perks based on their contribution to the business.\n\nTudigo provides an opportunity for community members to play an active role in the success of local businesses, contributing to the economic growth and vitality of their towns or neighborhoods. By encouraging donations and financial support, Tudigo helps create a sense of community and cooperation among individuals and businesses.\n\nOverall, Tudigo serves as a valuable platform for individuals and communities in France who are interested in making a positive impact on local businesses and contributing to their development.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 'tudigo', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(387, 'Anaxago', '/platformLogo/Anaxago.png', '[\"France\"]', '[\"Equity\"]', '[\"Real estate\",\"SME\"]', '2012', '13000878', '[\"French\"]', NULL, 'https://www.anaxago.com/', '1,000 EUR', '4-7%', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Anaxago is a crowdfunding platform based in France that primarily focuses on equity investments in the real estate and SME industries. Founded in 2012, the platform serves as a hub for investors seeking alternative ways to invest and offers unique investment opportunities in these sectors. Anaxago operates primarily in French language and can be accessed through their website, https://www.anaxago.com/.\n\nOne of the distinctive features of Anaxago is its low minimum investment requirement of 1,000 EUR, making it accessible to a wide range of investors. Additionally, the platform advertises a potential return on investment ranging from 4-7%, which can be an attractive prospect for those seeking higher returns in their investment portfolio.\n\nAnaxago offers investment opportunities in both real estate and startups, allowing investors to diversify their investment portfolios and potentially tap into emerging markets. This flexibility provides investors with the ability to choose investments that align with their preferences and risk tolerance.\n\nWhile the platform primarily operates in France, it offers an opportunity for international investors who are interested in the French market. By connecting investors with vetted opportunities, Anaxago aims to facilitate the investment process and provide a transparent and secure platform for both investors and projects seeking funding.\n\nOverall, Anaxago serves as a platform for investors to connect with unique investment opportunities in real estate and startups, with the potential for attractive returns. By providing a low minimum investment requirement and a diverse range of investment options, Anaxago aims to cater to a wide range of investors looking to diversify their portfolios.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 'anaxago', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(388, 'Lendahand', '/platformLogo/Lendahand.png', '[\"Netherlands\"]', '[\"Equity\"]', '[\"SME\"]', '2012', '55711766, ECSP', '[\"English\",\"Dutch\"]', NULL, 'https://www.lendahand.com/en-EU', '50 EUR', '7%', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Lendahand is a crowdfunding platform founded in the Netherlands in 2012. It offers individual lenders the opportunity to invest in small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) and entrepreneurs in developing economies. The platform operates on an equity investment type, allowing lenders to become shareholders in the businesses they invest in.\n\nLendahand focuses on combining social impact with financial return, making it an attractive option for those who want to make a positive difference while also garnering financial benefits. The platform primarily operates in the SME industry, supporting businesses in developing economies that may have limited access to traditional funding sources.\n\nLendahand\'s website is available in both English and Dutch, making it accessible to a wide range of potential investors. The minimum investment amount is 50 EUR, providing an opportunity for individuals with varying financial capacities to participate.\n\nThe advertised return on investments through Lendahand is 0.07, indicating the potential financial benefits investors can expect. However, it\'s important to note that investment returns may vary and are subject to market conditions and the success of the invested businesses.\n\nResidents of the European Union, Schengen zone, and the United Kingdom are eligible to invest through Lendahand. To sign up, potential investors need to provide a valid ID card, driver\'s license, or passport, as well as a bank statement copy not older than three months for non-Dutch bank account holders.\n\nOverall, Lendahand offers a socially impactful and sustainable crowdfunding platform for individuals looking to support SMEs and entrepreneurs in developing economies, while also earning potential financial returns on their investments.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Residents of EU, Schengen zone and the UK. You’ll need to provide a valid ID card, driver’s license, or passport as well as a bank statement copy not older than three months (for non-Dutch bank account holders)', 'lendahand', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(389, 'Oneplanetcrowd', '/platformLogo/Oneplanetcrowd.png', '[\"Netherlands\"]', '[\"Equity\"]', '[\"Green energy\"]', '2012', '61093904', '[\"English\",\"Dutch\"]', NULL, 'https://www.oneplanetcrowd.com/', '250 EUR', '6%', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Oneplanetcrowd is a crowdfunding platform based in the Netherlands, specializing in equity investments in the green energy industry. Established in 2012, the platform is a part of StartGreen Capital, a financial group that has been investing in sustainable companies and energy projects since 2005. With a strong network of partners including DGI Europe, Econnetic, and AS..., Oneplanetcrowd works closely with these organizations to connect investors with viable green energy projects.\n\nThe platform supports investments in both English and Dutch languages, catering to both domestic and international investors. The minimum investment required is 250 EUR, with an advertised return of 0.06. This makes it accessible to a wide range of individuals who are interested in supporting the green energy sector and seeking financial returns.\n\nTo invest as a private individual, one must have a bank account in the SEPA area, be at least 18 years old, and be a resident or have the nationality of a country in the SEPA area or the Caribbean Netherlands. For business customers, the representative must meet the requirements of a private investor, and the company must be a Dutch legal entity (sole trader, foundation, BV, or VOF) established in the Netherlands.\n\nWith its focus on green energy and its commitment to responsible investing, Oneplanetcrowd offers individuals and businesses the opportunity to support and participate in sustainable projects that have a positive impact on the environment and society. Its partnership with StartGreen Capital adds credibility to the platform, further attracting investors who are seeking ethical and financially rewarding investment opportunities.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A private investor must:— Have a bank account with a bank in the SEPA area, and click here to view the list of countries in the SEPA area — Be at least 18 years old, and — Be a resident in the SEPA area or the Caribbean Netherlands, and/or have the nationality of a country in the SEPA area or the Caribbean Netherlands.As a business customer, the representative must meet the requirements of a private investor, and in addition the company must:— Be a Dutch legal entity for sole trader, foundation, BV or VOF, and — Be established in the Netherlands.', 'oneplanetcrowd', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(390, 'Citizenergy', '/platformLogo/Citizenergy.png', '[\"Portugal\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"Green energy\"]', '2012', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://citizenergy.eu/', '1 EUR', 'N/A', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Citizenergy is a crowdfunding platform based in Portugal that specializes in P2P lending for green energy projects. Founded in 2012, it aims to promote cross-border investment in sustainable energy and provide information on opportunities from crowdfunding platforms and other sources.\n\nAs a recipient of European Union funding, Citizenergy has established itself as a pioneer in the field of sustainable energy crowdfunding. Their website, accessible at https://citizenergy.eu/, offers a user-friendly platform where investors can participate with a minimum investment of just 1 EUR.\n\nUnfortunately, the overview does not provide specific details about the advertised return on investments, leaving it unclear what potential investors can expect in terms of financial gain. However, the emphasis of Citizenergy lies in fostering investments in sustainable energy projects, which aligns with the growing demand for environmentally friendly solutions.\n\nOne notable feature of Citizenergy is its commitment to providing information on sustainable energy initiatives from a variety of sources, including both crowdfunding platforms and other relevant organizations. This expansive approach allows investors to gain a comprehensive understanding of available opportunities and make informed investment decisions.\n\nIn terms of eligibility, there is no information provided about who can invest in Citizenergy. It would be helpful to know if the platform is limited to residents of Portugal or if it is open to investors from around the world.\n\nOverall, Citizenergy presents itself as a pioneering crowdfunding platform that is dedicated to promoting sustainable energy projects and attracting cross-border investment. With its user-friendly platform and commitment to providing comprehensive information, it offers an exciting opportunity for individuals interested in supporting the green energy transition.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 'citizenergy', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(391, 'Zltymelon', '/platformLogo/Zltymelon.png', '[\"Slovakia\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"SME\"]', '2012', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://www.zltymelon.sk/', '25 EUR', 'N/A', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Anyone can invest in Zltymelon as long as they are at least 18 years old and have a bank account within the European Union. The platform primarily caters to individuals looking to invest in small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) through peer-to-peer lending.\n\nZltymelon was founded in 2012 in Slovakia and is a crowdfunding platform that aims to provide individuals with the opportunity to lend money directly to SMEs, bypassing traditional financial intermediaries. By eliminating unnecessary intermediaries, Zltymelon allows borrowers to access loans at more favorable terms, while investors can potentially earn higher returns on their investments.\n\nThe platform attracts investors with a minimum investment requirement of 25 EUR, providing an accessible entry point for individuals looking to participate in P2P lending. However, the advertised return rate is not provided, so investors may not have a clear understanding of the potential returns they can expect.\n\nZltymelon\'s website, available at https://www.zltymelon.sk/, provides an online platform where investors can browse and select various SME projects to invest in. The platform is available in multiple languages, although the specific languages offered are not mentioned in the provided information.\n\nOverall, Zltymelon offers a crowdfunding platform that enables individuals to invest in SMEs through P2P lending, providing borrowers with more favorable loan terms and potentially offering investors a chance to increase their money\'s value.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 'zltymelon', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(392, 'LightFin', '/platformLogo/LightFin.png', '[\"Germany\"]', '[\"Equity\",\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"Real estate\",\"SME\"]', '2012', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://www.lightfin.de/', '250 EUR', 'N/A', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Anyone can invest in LightFin as long as they meet the minimum investment requirement of 250 EUR. The platform primarily focuses on equity and P2P lending investments in the real estate and SME industries. LightFin was founded in Germany in 2012 and operates in the country. \n\nLightFin serves as a bridge between companies looking for capital and investors by utilizing the internet. It differentiates itself from other crowdfunding platforms by offering customized financial solutions to companies and their shareholders. \n\nThe platform\'s advertised return is not specified, suggesting that it may vary depending on the investment opportunity. LightFin\'s website provides further information and details about their services. \n\nOverall, LightFin aims to facilitate investment opportunities for individuals interested in the real estate and SME industries. It provides a convenient online platform where investors can connect with capital-seeking companies.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 'lightfin', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(393, 'Finexkap', '/platformLogo/Finexkap.png', '[\"France\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"SME\"]', '2012', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://www.finexkap.com/', '1 EUR', 'N/A', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Anyone can invest in Finexkap, including individuals and institutional investors. The platform specifically targets Very Small Enterprises (VSEs) and Small and Medium-sized Enterprises (SMEs) in France. Finexkap offers Peer-to-Peer (P2P) lending as an investment type, allowing investors to lend money directly to these businesses.\n\nFounded in 2012, Finexkap aims to provide a quick and simple solution for cash flow problems faced by VSEs and SMEs. The platform has gained experience and success over the years, financing more than 2.5 million invoices and counting.\n\nThe minimum investment on Finexkap is as low as 1 EUR, making it accessible to a wide range of investors. However, the specific advertised return on investment is not provided in the information given.\n\nWhile the overview does not mention the languages supported by the platform, the website indicates that it is available in both French and English, suggesting a bilingual option for investors.\n\nOverall, Finexkap serves as a crowdfunding platform that focuses on P2P lending for VSEs and SMEs in France. It provides a simple and fast solution for cash flow problems, allowing investors to support these businesses while potentially earning a return on their investment.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 'finexkap', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(394, 'Look&Fin', '/platformLogo/Look&Fin.png', '[\"Belgium\",\"France\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"Real estate\",\"SME\"]', '2012', 'N/A', '[\"French\",\"Dutch\"]', NULL, 'https://www.lookandfin.com/fr/', '100 EUR', '5%', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Look&Fin is a crowdfunding platform that operates in Belgium and France. Established in 2012, the platform focuses on P2P lending as an investment type, catering to the real estate and SME industries. Look&Fin provides an alternative financing solution for companies by facilitating direct funding from retail and institutional investors, thereby eliminating the need for intermediaries. To date, the platform has successfully facilitated €180 million in loans to 500 SMEs. \n\nLook&Fin prides itself on being an approved Alternative Financing Platform by the FSMA (Financial Services and Markets Authority). This endorsement signifies its credibility and compliance with regulatory standards. The platform welcomes individuals and legal entities with the legal capacity to contract, regardless of their nationality or tax residency, to invest on their platform. \n\nInvestors can participate in Look&Fin with a minimum investment of €100. The advertised return on investments is 0.05, providing an opportunity for potential financial growth. The platform is available in French and Dutch languages, catering to a wide range of investors in the region. \n\nOverall, Look&Fin offers a user-friendly and transparent crowdfunding platform for investment in the real estate and SME sectors. By connecting companies directly with investors, Look&Fin aims to provide a streamlined financing process while offering individuals and organizations the opportunity to generate returns on their investments.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 'The services offered by Look&Fin are exclusively intended for adults or legal entities with the legal capacity to contract, regardless of their nationality or tax residence.', 'look&fin', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 0