(427, 'Qredits', '/platformLogo/Qredits.png', '[\"Netherlands\"]', '[\"Debt\"]', '[\"SME\"]', '2009', 'N/A', '[\"Dutch\",\"English\"]', NULL, 'https://qredits.com/', '1 EUR', 'N/A', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Qredits is a crowdfunding platform based in the Netherlands that was founded in 2009. It focuses on offering credit, training, and coaching to small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) throughout the country. By providing these resources, Qredits aims to support entrepreneurs in the Netherlands and help them succeed in their business ventures.\n\nUnlike many other crowdfunding platforms, Qredits operates on a debt-based investment model. This means that individuals or corporations that invest in projects through Qredits will not receive equity in return, but rather expect repayment of the invested amount with interest over a specified period of time.\n\nThe platform is available in both Dutch and English languages, making it accessible to a wider audience. The minimum investment amount on Qredits is relatively low at just 1 EUR, allowing individuals and businesses of all sizes to participate.\n\nOne unique aspect of Qredits is that it does not operate with a profit motive. Instead, the platform reinvests all of its proceeds into providing support, such as training and coaching, for entrepreneurs. This approach aligns with the platform\'s mission to empower and assist SMEs in the Netherlands.\n\nOverall, Qredits offers an opportunity for personal and corporate investors to contribute to the growth and success of SMEs in the Netherlands through debt-based crowdfunding. With its focus on providing support and resources, Qredits aims to make a positive impact on the entrepreneurial landscape of the country.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Personal, Corporate', 'qredits', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
