(440, 'Twino', '/platformLogo/Twino.png', '[\"Latvia\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"Real estate\"]', '2009', 'Investment brokerage company license issued by the Financial and Capital Market Commission', '[\"English\",\"German\",\"Latvian\"]', NULL, 'https://www.twino.eu/en/', '10 EUR', '10%', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Twino is a P2P lending crowdfunding platform based in Latvia. Founded in 2009, it has focused on the real estate industry, connecting everyday individuals with investment opportunities typically limited to banks and brokerages. The platform, available in English, German, and Latvian, aims to provide a safe and secure environment for investors.\n\nWith a minimum investment of just 10 EUR, Twino offers an accessible entry point for individuals looking to invest in real estate projects. The advertised return on investment is 0.1%, providing potential earnings for investors. \n\nTwino has disrupted the traditional investment services industry by democratizing access to investment opportunities. Previously limited to institutional investors, these opportunities are now available to the average person. This has opened up possibilities for individuals to diversify their investment portfolios and potentially generate income from real estate ventures.\n\nIn order to invest on Twino, individuals must be at least 18 years old and citizens and residents of a European Economic Area country. Legal entities registered in Latvia are also eligible to invest on the platform.\n\nWith its user-friendly website and commitment to safety and security, Twino offers a convenient and transparent platform for individuals to engage in P2P lending and build their investment portfolios in the real estate sector.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 'In order to invest on TWINO, an individual investor must be at least 18 years old and a citizen and resident of a European Economic Area country. In addition, investors can choose to invest via a legal entity (only entities registered in Latvia)