ate rental businesses. Its carefully selected properties and attractive returns make it an appealing option for those seeking alternative investment opportunities.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 'You must be at least 18 years old and have a bank account.', 'inrento', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(470, 'Income Marketplace', '/platformLogo/Income Marketplace.png', '[\"Estonia\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"Personal loans\"]', '2020', '16014116', NULL, NULL, 'https://getincome.com/', '10 EUR', '11,81%', '6,032', '[\"N/A\"]', '50,593,388 EUR', 'N/A', 'Income Marketplace is a crowdfunding platform based in Estonia that specializes in P2P lending. Founded in 2020, the platform focuses on the personal loans industry, allowing investors to invest in loans from around the world. The platform\'s website, accessible through https://getincome.com/, provides all the necessary information and features to facilitate the investment process.\n\nIncome Marketplace sets a minimum investment amount of 10 EUR, making it accessible to a wide range of investors. The advertised return stands at 0.1181, attracting potential investors looking for profitable opportunities.\n\nTo be eligible to invest, individuals must meet certain requirements. They need to have a bank account in one of the countries within the European Economic Area (EEA) and possess relevant identification documents such as an EEA country-issued passport, ID card, or residence permit. Additionally, investors must be at least 18 years old and provide a copy of their identification documents to the Income Company.\n\nBy providing a platform for P2P lending, Income Marketplace offers investors the opportunity to diversify their portfolios and potentially achieve attractive returns. The platform aims to connect borrowers and investors from around the globe, serving as an intermediary that facilitates secure and transparent transactions. With its user-friendly website and accessible minimum investment, Income Marketplace strives to create a seamless experience for investors interested in the personal loans industry.', 0, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'Eligibility requirements:— Have a bank account in one of the countries of the European Economic Area; — EEA country-issued passport, ID card, or residence permit; — Be at least 18 years old; — Provide a copy of identification documents to the Income Company.', 'incomemarketplace', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(471, 'Heavyfinance', '/platformLogo/Heavyfinance.png', '[\"Lithuania\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"Farming\"]', '2020', '305576227', NULL, NULL, 'https://heavyfinance.com/?utm_offer=General&click_id=84b72e78-4ada-4c30-8e6a-434609a77441', '100 EUR', '12%', 'N/A', '[\"Credit card\",\"Bank transfer\"]', '33,000,000 EUR', '30 months', 'HeavyFinance is a crowdfunding platform based in Lithuania that specializes in P2P lending within the farming industry. Founded in 2020, HeavyFinance provides a marketplace for investors and businesses that rely on heavy equipment. \n\nThe platform offers investment opportunities that are backed by heavy equipment as collateral, ensuring the security of investments. This allows investors to support agricultural projects while mitigating risk. \n\nInvestors can join the HeavyFinance platform by registering and verifying their identity through the verification process. Both natural persons who have reached the age of majority and legal entities are eligible to invest through the platform. However, residents of countries on the sanction list of the EU and the United Nations are not permitted to register.\n\nWith a minimum investment requirement of 100 EUR, HeavyFinance provides accessibility to a wide range of investors. The platform advertises a return of 0.12, which suggests the potential for a favorable ROI.\n\nOverall, HeavyFinance brings together investors and agricultural businesses, providing a space for P2P lending within the farming industry. With a focus on heavy equipment as collateral, the platform ensures security and offers investment opportunities to support agricultural projects.', 1, 0, 1, 0, 1, 1, 'Investing using the HeavyFinance crowdfunding platform is permitted to natural persons who have reached the age of majority and all legal entities. Prior to making an investment, it is important to confirm your identity via the verification process.Registering on HeavyFinance is not allowed only for residents of countries on the sanction list of the EU and the United Nations.', 'heavyfinance', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(472, 'Max Crowdfund', '/platformLogo/Max Crowdfund.png', '[\"Netherlands\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"Real estate\"]', '2020', '19000066', '[\"English\",\"Dutch\"]', NULL, 'https://maxcrowdfund.com/en/?click_id=70e0c9c9-2fbb-435a-93d9-69edd5c97c2b&adinventory_name=CrowdSpace&adinventory_id=pa6833', '100 EUR', '10%', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', '48,929,800 EUR', 'N/A', 'Max Crowdfund is a crowdfunding platform based in the Netherlands that specializes in P2P lending for real estate investments. Founded in 2020, the platform offers investment opportunities in property asset-backed projects that meet high investment criteria.\n\nThe platform operates in both English and Dutch, allowing investors from different countries to participate. The minimum investment required is 100 EUR, making it accessible to a wide range of individuals.\n\nMax Crowdfund advertises a return of 0.1, providing investors with the potential for a profitable investment. However, it should be noted that returns on investments can vary depending on the specific projects.\n\nTo ensure the security and legality of transactions, investors must be over 18 years old and have an authorized bank account. They are also required to submit and have their Know Your Client (KYC) documents approved, as well as link their bank account to their Max Crowdfund account. Additionally, there may be country-specific restrictions that prevent certain nationalities from participating in certain investment products.\n\nMax Crowdfund\'s focus on regulatory compliance and transparency aligns with its commitment to prevent money laundering, tax evasion, and illegal activities. This ensures a trustworthy and secure environment for investors.\n\nOverall, Max Crowdfund offers a user-friendly platform for individuals looking to invest in real estate projects, with a range of investment opportunities and a strong emphasis on regulatory compliance.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Investors must be over 18 and have an authorized bank account, which means their Know Your Client (KYC) documents must be submitted and approved and a bank account must be linked to their account. There are country specific restrictions and certain nationalities may be prevented from participating in certain investment products. This measure aims to prevent money laundering, tax evasion and other illegal activities, in line with our commitment to regulatory compliance and transparency.', 'maxcrowdfund', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(473, 'Impact Funding', '/platformLogo/Impact Funding.png', '[\"Germany\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"Green energy\"]', '2019', 'HRB 214384', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.impact-funding.org/?s_id=1236308798X53318C378474068T', '100 EUR', 'N/A', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Impact Funding is a crowdfunding platform based in Germany that specializes in P2P lending for green energy projects. Established in 2019, the platform supports entrepreneurs who have innovative ideas that can positively impact the environment. They strive to support those who challenge conventional norms and have a vision for a better world.\n\nAs a P2P lending platform, Impact Funding connects lenders with borrowers in the green energy industry. Individuals and businesses alike can invest in these projects by providing a minimum investment of 100 EUR. The platform provides an opportunity for both personal and corporate investors to contribute to the growth of sustainable energy initiatives.\n\nWhile the exact advertised return is not mentioned, the focus of Impact Funding is to make a positive impact rather than solely emphasizing financial gains. The website offers more information about the available projects and how to get involved. The platform encourages those who want to support renewable energy and contribute to a greener future to participate in their crowdfunding campaigns.\n\nOverall, Impact Funding provides a platform for individuals and businesses to invest in P2P lending for green energy projects in Germany. Their mission is to support entrepreneurs who have a passion for creating a better world through sustainable practices and encourage investment from both personal and corporate entities.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Personal, Corporate', 'impactfunding', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(474, 'Ener2Crowd', '/platformLogo/Ener2Crowd.png', '[\"Italy\"]', '[\"Debt\"]', '[\"Green energy\"]', '2018', '16568', '[\"Italian\",\"Spanish\",\"English\"]', NULL, 'https://www.ener2crowd.com/it/home?customxyz=10249a995444e72e770f38c991f390', '250 EUR', '4-5%', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Ener2Crowd is a crowdfunding platform based in Italy that focuses on debt investments in the green energy industry. Founded in 2018, it is the first Italian platform dedicated to sustainable investments.\n\nThe platform supports multiple languages including Italian, Spanish, and English, making it accessible to a wider range of investors. Ener2Crowd\'s website (https://www.ener2crowd.com/it/home?customxyz=10249a995444e72e770f38c991f390) provides detailed information and resources for potential investors.\n\nEner2Crowd allows both private individuals and corporate investors to participate in lending capital to large and significant Italian companies that are committed to developing green energy projects. This gives investors the opportunity to support environmentally friendly initiatives while also earning a return on their investment.\n\nThe minimum investment on the Ener2Crowd platform is 250 EUR, making it accessible to a wide range of investors. The platform advertises a return on investment of 4-5%, which may vary depending on the specific project and investment terms.\n\nOverall, Ener2Crowd offers a unique opportunity for individuals and institutions to support sustainable investments in the green energy sector in Italy. By leveraging the power of crowdfunding, the platform aims to drive positive change in the environment while providing financial benefits to its investors.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 'Corporate and private investors', 'ener2crowd', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(475, 'Concrete Investing', '/platformLogo/Concrete Investing.png', '[\"Italy\"]', '[\"Equity\"]', '[\"Real estate\"]', '2018', '20405', '[\"Italian\"]', NULL, 'https://www.concreteinvesting.com/?tclid=10268d7d566db0dcd90bd6b05602f8', '5,000 EUR', 'N/A', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Concrete Investing is an equity crowdfunding platform based in Italy. It was founded in 2018 and focuses specifically on real estate investments. The platform is authorized by CONSOB, Italy\'s financial market regulator, ensuring a high level of transparency and security for investors.\n\nThe main objective of Concrete Investing is to provide a platform where users can view and evaluate real estate investment opportunities. These opportunities are carefully selected and presented to investors, allowing them to invest in real estate transactions quickly and conveniently.\n\nInvestors on Concrete Investing can expect to invest a minimum of 5,000 EUR. However, the advertised return is not available based on the provided information. It is important to note that investors must be of legal age and possess an Italian tax code. Additionally, investors are required to complete an appropriateness questionnaire to assess their understanding of financial concepts, risk management, and their ability to withstand potential capital losses.\n\nThe website of Concrete Investing is available in Italian, indicating that it primarily caters to Italian investors. However, it is not explicitly mentioned whether the platform accepts international investors.\n\nOverall, Concrete Investing offers an authorized and regulated platform for investors interested in real estate equity crowdfunding. Through a transparent and streamlined process, individuals can access selected real estate opportunities and potentially grow their investment portfolio.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Anyone can invest in equity crowdfunding through Concrete Investing. The only two conditions are the age of majority and the possession of an Italian tax code. For investment purposes, the completion of an appropriateness questionnaire is required, the purpose of which is to verify the Investor’s basic knowledge of financial concepts, his understanding of the risks associated with the Investment and his ability to face the potential loss of the capital.', 'concreteinvesting', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(476, 'EstateGuru', '/platformLogo/EstateGuru.png', '[\"Estonia\",\"Latvia\",\"Lithuania\",\"United Kingdom\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"Real estate\"]', '2018', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://estateguru.co/get-started/?publisherId=TCpa6833&partnerId=1&tmtData=fed651e7-a0c3-4a53-800c-54ff6d8e3d62', '50 EUR', '10.68%', '157,112', '[\"N/A\"]', '711,391,541 EUR', 'N/A', 'EstateGuru is a crowdfunding platform founded in 2018 that operates in Estonia, Latvia, Lithuania, and the United Kingdom. Specializing in P2P lending within the real estate industry, EstateGuru offers short-term, property-backed loans. \n\nInvestors can participate in this platform with a minimum investment of 50 EUR and can expect an advertised return of 10.68%. To start lending through EstateGuru, individuals must be at least 18 years old and have a bank account in any of the EEA member states or Switzerland. Additionally, EstateGuru conducts \"know your customer\" checks before investors can begin building their investment portfolios.\n\nAs the leading European marketplace for property-backed loans, EstateGuru provides investors with an opportunity to diversify their investment portfolios and potentially earn attractive returns. The platform creates a connection between lenders and borrowers, allowing individuals to directly invest their funds in real estate projects. \n\nWith an easily accessible website, investors can easily get started by visiting https://estateguru.co/get-started/?publisherId=TCpa6833&partnerId=1&tmtData=fed651e7-a0c3-4a53-800c-54ff6d8e3d62. EstateGuru offers a user-friendly experience, making it convenient for investors to navigate through the platform and support real estate development projects.', 1, 0, 1, 0, 1, 0, 'You must be at least 18 years old and have a bank account in any of the EEA member states or Switzerland in order to lend through Estateguru. We also have to perform certain “know your customer” checks before you can start building your portfolio.', 'estateguru', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(477, 'Trusters', '/platformLogo/Trusters.png', '[\"Italy\"]', '[\"Debt\"]', '[\"Real estate\"]', '2017', '77409', '[\"Italian\"]', NULL, 'https://www.trusters.it/?custom=1024fbe06b69f0b87bb9cba9743c60%7C1255%7C%7C%7C%7C%7C%7C%7C', '250 EUR', '9,6%', 'N/A', '[\"Credit card\",\"Bank transfer\"]', '43,800,000 EUR', 'N/A', 'Trusters is a crowdfunding platform based in Italy, founded in 2017. It specializes in debt-based investments in the real estate industry. The platform operates in the Italian language and is accessible through their website: https://www.trusters.it/?custom=1024fbe06b69f0b87bb9cba9743c60%7C1255%7C%7C%7C%7C%7C%7C%7C.\n\nTrusters aims to introduce a new way of financing that is open to everyone, allowing individuals and companies to participate in real estate investment opportunities. The platform was developed by experts with extensive experience in the real estate sector.\n\nThe minimum investment required on Trusters is 250 EUR, providing an affordable entry point for potential investors. The advertised return on investments stands at 0.096, highlighting the potential profitability of participating in debt-based real estate projects on the platform.\n\nTrusters welcomes both physical individuals and legal entities to register on their platform. Before creating an account, users are given the option to choose between an individual or company account type, catering to the needs and preferences of a wide range of investors.\n\nOverall, Trusters offers a convenient and inclusive platform for individuals and companies seeking to diversify their investment portfolios by participating in debt-based real estate projects. The platform\'s user-friendly interface and affordable minimum investment make it an attractive option for those interested in the Italian real estate market.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Both physical and legal persons can register on Trusters. Before creating your account, you can choose whether to do it as an individual or as a company.', 'trus