(478, 'PeerBerry', '/platformLogo/PeerBerry.png', '[\"Lithuania\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"Real estate\",\"SME\",\"Personal loans\"]', '2017', 'No', '[\"English\",\"German\",\"Spanish\"]', NULL, 'https://peerberry.com/?utm_source=targetcircle&tmtData=94807463-1963-4b53-b79e-998629dc1ce3', '10 EUR', '9—12%', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'PeerBerry is a crowdfunding platform based in Lithuania that specializes in P2P lending. It was founded in 2017 and offers investment opportunities in the real estate, SME, and personal loan industries. The platform is available in multiple languages, including English, German, and Spanish. \n\nWith a minimum investment of just 10 EUR, PeerBerry provides an accessible and user-friendly investment experience. They boast a competitive advertised return of 9-12%, making it an attractive option for investors seeking higher yields. \n\nOne of PeerBerry\'s key strengths is its focus on client satisfaction. They prioritize the needs of their investors and provide them with cutting-edge investment tools to enhance their experience. The platform emphasizes transparency and offers detailed information about each investment opportunity.\n\nIn terms of who can invest, both individuals and companies are welcome to join PeerBerry. However, there are certain criteria to meet. Investors must be at least 18 years old and can only deposit funds from credit, payment, or electronic money institutions within the European Union or third countries with AML/CFT systems equivalent to the EU.\n\nOverall, PeerBerry aims to provide an alternative investment marketplace for individuals and companies looking to diversify their portfolios and achieve higher returns in a secure and transparent manner.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Individuals and companies can become investors at PeerBerry. You must be at least 18 years old and that we only accept deposits from the credit, payment, or electronic money institutions within the European Union or third countries currently considered to have AML/CFT systems equivalent to the EU.', 'peerberry', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(479, 'AxiaFunder', '/platformLogo/AxiaFunder.png', '[\"United Kingdom\"]', '[\"Equity\"]', '[\"Litigation\"]', '2017', 'FRN 603332', '[\"English\"]', NULL, 'https://www.axiafunder.com/circlewise.html?offer_sid=ua4e05&tmt_data=a455224a-5b2e-41d3-ae38-3fea8fe9fa03&r=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.axiafunder.com%2Finvestments%3Fclick_id%3Da455224a-5b2e-41d3-ae38-3fea8fe9fa03%26utm_campaign%3DCrowdSpace&tmt_ufp=649b24bf7ff35079da9995229a0b0e8543f49f836e995747df8fca49f2bcc3a1', '1,000 GBP', 'No%', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'AxiaFunder is a crowdfunding platform based in the United Kingdom that specializes in equity investments in the litigation industry. Founded in 2017, the platform allows investors to connect with carefully vetted commercial litigation investment opportunities that have the potential to generate attractive risk-adjusted returns.\n\nThe platform is available in English and offers a minimum investment of 1,000 GBP. While the advertised return is not specified, AxiaFunder aims to provide investors with profitable opportunities in the litigation sector.\n\nAxiaFunder caters exclusively to certified high net worth individuals, self-certified sophisticated investors, and professional investors in the UK. This ensures that only eligible and knowledgeable investors have access to the investment opportunities provided by the platform.\n\nBy focusing specifically on the litigation industry, AxiaFunder offers investors a unique chance to participate in legal cases and potentially benefit from successful outcomes. This niche approach allows investors to diversify their portfolios and potentially earn returns from a sector not commonly associated with crowdfunding.\n\nAs an online platform, AxiaFunder provides a user-friendly experience and a transparent investment process. Investors can access detailed information about each investment opportunity and make informed decisions. By connecting with AxiaFunder, individuals can explore the potential of litigation investments and potentially achieve attractive risk-adjusted returns.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 'In the UK, AxiaFunder offers investment opportunities to the following categories of investors only: certified high net worth individuals, self-certified sophisticated investors and professional investors.', 'axiafunder', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(480, 'Blend Network', '/platformLogo/Blend Network.png', '[\"United Kingdom\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"Real estate\"]', '2017', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://blendnetwork.com/?utm_source=crowdspace&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=banner', '1,000 GBP', 'N/A', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Blend Network is a crowdfunding platform based in the United Kingdom that specializes in P2P lending in the real estate industry. Founded in 2017, Blend Network connects lenders directly with borrowers, providing an opportunity for individuals to invest in property-secured loans. \n\nThe platform allows lenders to participate with an investment as low as £1,000, making it accessible to a wide range of investors. While the advertised return is not provided in the given information, lenders have the potential to earn up to 12% per annum on their investments.\n\nOne of the key features of Blend Network is that all loans are secure against a first-charge on the property, providing a level of security for lenders. This reduces the risk associated with their investments. \n\nBlend Network\'s online platform offers a user-friendly experience, allowing lenders to easily browse and select investment opportunities. All borrowers are carefully screened and assessed by Blend Network to ensure the quality and viability of the projects.\n\nOverall, Blend Network provides a platform for investors to diversify their portfolios and invest in property-secured loans. With its minimum investment requirement, focus on real estate, and potential returns, it appeals to individuals looking for opportunities to earn attractive returns in the UK crowdfunding market.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 'blendnetwork', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(481, 'Brickstarter', '/platformLogo/Brickstarter.png', '[\"Spain\"]', '[\"Equity\"]', '[\"Real estate\"]', '2017', '14766591', '[\"Spanish\",\"English\"]', NULL, 'https://brickstarter.com/', '50 EUR', '5%', 'N/A', '[\"Credit card\",\"Bank transfer\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Brickstarter is a Spanish crowdfunding platform that primarily focuses on real estate investments in the vacation rental industry. Founded in 2017, it offers individuals and companies registered in Spain the opportunity to invest in equity-based projects. The platform allows investors to contribute a minimum amount of 50 EUR towards various real estate ventures.\n\nBrickstarter operates in both Spanish and English, making it accessible to a wider audience. Its website, located at https://brickstarter.com/, provides a user-friendly interface to cater to the needs of potential investors. Advertised returns on investments through Brickstarter stand at 0.05, providing a promising return on investment for participants.\n\nThe platform distinguishes itself by specializing in vacation rental properties, recognizing the growing demand and potential profitability of this industry. By focusing on this niche market, Brickstarter offers investors an opportunity to diversify their portfolios and take advantage of the increasing popularity of vacation rentals.\n\nHowever, Brickstarter imposes certain eligibility criteria for investors. Participation is open to individuals who are of legal age and possess Spanish or EU nationality, as well as to companies registered in Spain.\n\nOverall, Brickstarter aims to democratize real estate investments by providing a transparent and accessible crowdfunding platform for investors interested in the vacation rental industry.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Individuals, of legal age, with Spanish or EU nationality. Companies registered in Spain.', 'brickstarter', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(482, 'Swaper', '/platformLogo/Swaper.png', '[\"Estonia\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"Personal loans\"]', '2016', '14726410', '[\"English\",\"German\"]', NULL, 'https://swaper.com/en?click_id=2f1d3b0e-9913-43dd-9fd9-811aa7c5d086', '10 EUR', '14%', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Swaper is a crowdfunding platform based in Estonia that specializes in P2P lending in the personal loans industry. Established in 2016, the platform provides individuals with the opportunity to invest in loans, with the potential to earn a maximum annual return of 16%. Swaper aims to provide a simple, easy, and transparent investment experience for its users.\n\nWith exponential growth since its inception, Swaper has garnered significant attention within the investing community. The platform has raised substantial funds, positioning itself as a major player in the industry.\n\nTo become an investor on Swaper, individuals must be at least 18 years old and residents of a country within the European Economic Area (EEA), Switzerland, or the UK. Additionally, investors must possess a bank account within one of these countries. However, at present, Swaper does not accept investors from Poland or private investors from Estonia. The definition of a resident extends to citizens, individuals with residence permits, and those registered as taxpayers within the specified regions.\n\nSwaper\'s website is available in both English and German, providing accessibility to a broader audience. The platform\'s minimum investment requirement is a mere 10 EUR, catering to a wide range of investors.\n\nOverall, Swaper offers a reliable and regulated crowdfunding platform for individuals looking to invest in the personal loans sector.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 'To become an investor, you need to be at least 18 years old, be a resident of a country in the European Economic Area (EEA), Switzerland or the UK and have a bank account with a bank situated in one of those countries. Currently, we do not accept investors from Poland and private investors from Estonia. An individual is recognized as a resident if he or she is a citizen, has a residence permit or is registered as a taxpayer in an EEA country, Switzerland or UK.', 'swaper', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(483, 'WIWIN', '/platformLogo/WIWIN.png', '[\"Germany\"]', '[\"Debt\"]', '[\"SME\",\"Green energy\"]', '2016', 'HRA 32940 USt', '[\"German\"]', NULL, 'https://wiwin.de/?utm_source=affiliate&utm_medium=53318&utm_campaign=financeads&s_id=1236307890X53318C231975540T', '500 EUR', '3.4% - 4.8%', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'WIWIN is a crowdfunding platform founded in Germany in 2016. It focuses on debt-based investments and operates in the SME industry, specifically in the green energy sector. The platform primarily offers its services to German residents, as investors must have their place of residence or registered office in the Federal Republic of Germany and be over 18 years old. However, it does not allow politically exposed persons, US citizens, and married couples to invest.\n\nWIWIN acts as an intermediary for capital investments, particularly in renewable energies, sustainable startups, and energy-efficient real estate. The platform provides an opportunity for individuals to invest in these sectors with a minimum investment amount of 500 EUR.\n\nThe platform\'s website is available in the German language, catering to the local market. It offers an advertised return ranging from 3.4% to 4.8%, making it an attractive investment option for those seeking a decent return on their investment.\n\nWIWIN\'s objective is to facilitate the progress of green energy and sustainability projects by connecting investors with businesses in need of funding. By providing a platform for individuals to support environmentally friendly initiatives, WIWIN aims to contribute to the growth of the green economy in Germany.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Anyone who has their place of residence or registered office in the Federal Republic of Germany and is over 18 years of age can invest in WIWIN. This does not apply to politically exposed persons, US citizens and married couples.', 'wiwin', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(484, 'DoFinance', '/platformLogo/DoFinance.png', '[\"Latvia\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"SME\"]', '2016', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://c.trackmytarget.com/?a=ic99f6&i=pa6833', '10 EUR', 'N/A', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'DoFinance is a crowdfunding platform based in Latvia. It was founded in 2016 and specializes in peer-to-peer lending for small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs). The platform aims to provide easy and smart investing options for individuals. \n\nWith a focus on P2P lending, DoFinance allows investors to lend money directly to SMEs looking for financing. This alternative investment option allows investors to diversify their portfolios and potentially earn attractive returns. \n\nDoFinance operates globally and is committed to being at the forefront of financial technology. It strives to provide the most advanced platform for investment management, making it convenient for users to invest and manage their funds. \n\nThe minimum investment required on the DoFinance platform is 10 EUR, making it accessible to a wide range of investors. However, the exact advertised return is not specified, so potential investors would need to further explore the platform to determine the expected returns on their investments. \n\nOverall, DoFinance offers individuals the opportunity to participate in P2P lending and support SMEs while potentially earning attractive returns on their investments.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 'dofinance', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(485, 'Viainvest', '/platformLogo/Viainvest.png', '[\"Czech Republic\",\"Latvia\",\"Poland\",\"Romania\",\"Spain\",\"Sweden\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"SME\"]', '2016', '06.06.08.735/538 — IBF license issued by the Financial and Capital Market Commission (FCMC)', '[\"English\",\"Latvian\"]', NULL, 'https://viainvest.com/?tmt_data=a4112dfa-d978-4afd-8c25-13111d81a1ee&utm_source=tracknet&utm_medium=affiliate&utm_campaign=regular', '50 EUR', '13%', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Viainvest is a crowdfunding platform that was founded in 2016 and is based in the Czech Republic, Latvia, Poland, Romania, Spain, and Sweden. It operates in the P2P lending industry and specializes in providing investment opportunities to small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs). The platform allows private investors, both individuals and legal entities, to invest in loans originated by non-banking lenders, specifically the VIA SMS Group and its subsidiaries.\n\nThe loans offered on Viainvest consist mainly of short-term loans, providing investors with opportunities for quick returns. The minimum investment required is 50 EUR, making it accessible to a wide range of investors. The platform advertises a return of 0.13, indicating a potentially lucrative investment opportunity.\n\nTo be eligible to invest on Viainvest, individuals must be at least 18 years old and have tax residency within one of the European countries, Switzerland, or the United Kingdom. The registration process involves providing personal information and making the first deposit to the VIAINVEST investor account. Once the personal information matches the bank information of the investor, the profile becomes active, and investing can begin.\n\nViainvest offers its services in English and Latvian, making it accessible to a broader international audience. The platform\'s website provides further information and allows potential investors to sign up and start investing.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'To begin investing as a private individual, you must be at least 18 years old and hold a tax residency within one of the European countries, Switzerland, or the United Kingdom. In order to start investing feel free to complete the registration process and make the first deposit to your VIAINVEST investor account. If personal information stated in your investor profile matches the bank information of the person transferring funds to the VIAINVEST platform, the investor profile becomes active and you are able to start investing.', 'viainvest', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(486, 'Soisy', '/platformLogo/Soisy.png', '[\"Italy\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"SME\"]', '2015', 'N/A', '[\"Italian\"]', NULL, 'https://www.soisy.it/investimenti-online/?custom=10254721351cf4d5f7d662ccd0a1af%7C1255%7C%7C%7C%7C%7C%7C%7C', '1 EUR', '5–8%', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Soisy is an Italian crowdfunding platform founded in 2015. It specializes in peer-to-peer lending for small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs). The platform operates exclusively in the Italian language, catering to the local market.\n\nSoisy functions as a marketplace for individuals and corporations to invest in SMEs. The minimum investment amount is only 1 EUR, making it accessible to a wide range of investors. The platform advertises a return on investment ranging from 5% to 8%, providing potential profitability for investors.\n\nThe core philosophy of Soisy is rooted in the principles of peer-to-peer collaboration and the sharing economy. By leveraging the power of the crowd, the platform aims to connect investors with promising SMEs in need of financial support. This model not only provides opportunities for investors to diversify their portfolio but also enables SMEs to access much-needed funding.\n\nBoth personal and corporate investors can participate in Soisy, allowing individuals and businesses to contribute to the growth of the Italian SME sector. This inclusive approach fosters economic development and stimulates job creation in Italy.\n\nTo learn more about Soisy and explore investment opportunities, interested individuals can visit their website at https://www.soisy.it/investimenti-online/?custom=10254721351cf4d5f7d662ccd0a1af%7C1255%7C%7C%7C%7C%7C%7C%7C.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Personal, Corporate', 'soisy', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
