(488, 'Kviku Finance', '/platformLogo/Kviku Finance.png', '[\"Cyprus\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"SME\",\"Personal loans\"]', '2013', 'HE 382807 ', NULL, NULL, 'https://kviku.finance/en/sign-up-bonus', '100 EUR', '12%', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Kviku Finance is a crowdfunding platform based in Cyprus that offers peer-to-peer lending opportunities. The platform specializes in providing loans to small and medium-sized enterprises (SME) as well as personal loans. It was founded in 2013 and is a part of the Kviku Group, an international financial holding company that collaborates with consumer lenders in both Europe and Asia.\n\nKviku Finance welcomes investors from both natural and legal persons. Natural persons must be of full legal capacity and possess a valid bank account within the European Union or in third countries that are acknowledged to have equivalent AML/CFT systems as the EU. Legal persons are also accepted as investors and must have a valid bank account within the European Union or in third countries meeting the equivalent AML/CFT criteria.\n\nThe minimum investment amount to participate on the Kviku Finance platform is 100 EUR. The platform advertises a return rate of 0.12, which refers to the investment yield or interest rate that investors can expect to earn.\n\nTo learn more about Kviku Finance and start investing, individuals can visit their website at https://kviku.finance/en/sign-up-bonus. The platform provides an opportunity for investors to support SMEs and individuals while potentially earning returns on their investments.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Kviku Finance accepts investments from both natural and legal persons. Natural persons must have full legal capacity to act as well as to have a valid bank account within the European Union or third countries that are currently considered as having equivalent AML/CFT systems to the EU.Legal persons must have a valid bank account within the European Union or third countries that are currently considered as having equivalent AML/CFT systems to the EU.', 'kvikufinance', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(489, 'Econeers', '/platformLogo/Econeers.png', '[\"Germany\"]', '[\"Equity\"]', '[\"Green energy\"]', '2013', 'DF-144-A25W-55', '[\"German\"]', NULL, 'https://www.econeers.de/?entryPoint=financeads&s_id=1236307096', '250 EUR', '6%', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Econeers is a German crowdfunding platform that focuses on green energy projects. Founded in 2013, Econeers provides an avenue for private and institutional investors to participate in sustainable projects related to the ecological and energy transition. The platform offers equity-based investments, allowing investors to become stakeholders in these projects.\n\nEconeers\' website, available only in German, serves as the hub for investors to explore and select projects to support. The minimum investment required is 250 euros, making it accessible for a wide range of investors. The platform offers an advertised return of 0.06, providing the potential for financial gains to investors.\n\nOne of the key features of Econeers is its inclusive investment policy. It welcomes individual investors, as well as corporations and partnerships such as AG, GmbH, KG. This openness allows a diverse range of investors to participate in the green energy sector, contributing towards a more sustainable future.\n\nWith its focus on green energy projects, Econeers addresses the growing demand for sustainable investments. By connecting investors with viable green projects, the platform provides an opportunity to support and contribute towards the energy transition. Econeers stands as a platform that bridges the gap between aspiring green projects and investors who are passionate about sustainability and environmental change.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Econeers is basically open to everyone over the age of 18. Private individuals as well as corporations and partnerships (e.g. AG, GmbH, KG) can invest.', 'econeers', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
