(513, 'BOLDYIELD', '/platformLogo/BOLDYIELD.png', '[\"Estonia\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"Real estate\",\"SME\"]', '2019', '14720152', '[\"English\"]', NULL, 'https://boldyield.com/', '100 EUR', '18%', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Boldyield is a peer-to-business crowdfunding platform that was founded in Estonia in 2019. The platform specializes in P2P lending for both real estate and cash-flow businesses. Its main objective is to connect investors with opportunities in the real estate and SME industries. \n\nAs a crowdfunding platform, Boldyield allows individuals and companies to invest in projects through its website, which is available in English. The minimum investment amount is 100 EUR, making it accessible to a wide range of investors. \n\nBoldyield advertises a return of 0.18, meaning that investors have the potential to earn a return on their investments. \n\nIn terms of eligibility, any person who is 18 years or older and has a European Economic Area bank account can invest on the platform. Companies with a bank account within the European Union are also eligible to invest. However, both individuals and companies must undergo a fully accepted Know Your Customer (KYC) process and comply with Anti-Money Laundering (AML) and Counter Terrorism Financing (CTF) risk policies before being able to invest on the Boldyield platform.\n\nOverall, Boldyield offers individuals and companies the opportunity to invest in real estate and cash-flow businesses through its peer-to-business crowdfunding platform. With a focus on accessibility and compliance, it aims to provide a safe and profitable investment experience for its users.', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Any person which is 18 years or older, who has a European Economic Area bank account can make investments on our platform. Companies with a bank account within the European Union (EU) can also invest. Both individuals and companies should be fully accepted according to our KYC, AML/CTF risk policies prior to place an investment on the BOLDYIELD platform.', 'boldyield', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(514, 'FinoMark', '/platformLogo/FinoMark.png', '[\"Lithuania\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"Real estate\",\"Startups\",\"SME\",\"Green energy\",\"Logistics\",\"Mortgages\"]', '2019', '305538582', '[\"English\",\"Lithuanian\"]', NULL, 'https://www.finomark.lt/en/', '25 EUR', '11%', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'FinoMark is a crowdfunding platform based in Lithuania that offers P2P lending opportunities for various industries including real estate, startups, small and medium enterprises (SMEs), green energy, logistics, and mortgages. Founded in 2019, FinoMark aims to streamline the funding process and provide a more efficient and value-added solution for both fundraisers and investors.\n\nThe platform is available in both English and Lithuanian languages, making it accessible to a wider range of users. FinoMark has a minimum investment requirement of 25 EUR, allowing individuals and corporations to participate in P2P lending.\n\nFinoMark advertises a return of 0.11, indicating the potential return on investment for participating in crowdfunding campaigns on the platform. This return rate may vary depending on the specific projects and investments made.\n\nThe main focus of FinoMark is to help businesses achieve their financial goals by connecting them with investors interested in funding their projects. Through the platform, fundraisers can access capital from a diverse pool of investors, while investors can explore various investment opportunities and diversify their portfolio.\n\nOverall, FinoMark provides a user-friendly crowdfunding platform that enables both personal and corporate investors to participate in P2P lending for a range of industries, ultimately facilitating the growth and success of businesses in Lithuania. More information can be found on their website at https://www.finomark.lt/en/.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Personal, Corporate', 'finomark', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(515, 'Genervest', '/platformLogo/Genervest.png', '[\"Netherlands\"]', '[\"Equity\",\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"Green energy\"]', '2019', '860783935', '[\"English\",\"Greek\",\"French\",\"Dutch\"]', NULL, 'https://genervest.org/', '10 EUR', 'N/A', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Anyone can invest in Genervest, from individuals to institutions, regardless of their location. The platform allows investors from all over the world to contribute to the growth of green energy projects. \n\nInvestment Type: \n\nGenervest offers two types of investment options: equity and peer-to-peer (P2P) lending. With the equity option, investors become shareholders in green energy projects, sharing in the profits and risks. P2P lending, on the other hand, allows investors to lend money directly to these projects, earning interest on their investment. \n\nIndustry: \n\nGenervest focuses specifically on the green energy industry, supporting projects that promote clean and sustainable energy sources. By investing in these projects, individuals can actively contribute to the global energy transition and help combat climate change. \n\nYear Founded: \n\nGenervest was established in 2019, making it a relatively new player in the crowdfunding market. However, its focus on green energy aligns with the increasing demand for environmentally conscious investment opportunities. \n\nLanguages: \n\nGenervest operates in multiple languages including English, Greek, French, and Dutch, ensuring accessibility to a diverse range of investors. \n\nWebsite and Minimum Investment: \n\nGenervest\'s website, located at https://genervest.org/, provides detailed information about the platform and investment opportunities. The minimum investment amount on the platform is set at 10 EUR, allowing individuals with varying financial capabilities to participate. \n\nAdvertised Return: \n\nThe overview does not provide specific information about the advertised return on investment, suggesting that it may vary depending on individual projects and investments. \n\nDescription: \n\nGenervest distinguishes itself as an ethical and socially responsible investment platform, providing investors the opportunity to grow their money while supporting the energy transition. By giving individuals the power to determine how their money is invested, Genervest promotes a sense of community and empowerment among its investors, or \"Genervestors,\" both big and small.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL, 'genervest', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
