(540, 'Crowdway', '/platformLogo/Crowdway.png', '[\"Poland\"]', '[\"Equity\"]', '[\"Startups\",\"SME\",\"Green energy\"]', '2015', 'in progress', '[\"Polish\"]', NULL, 'https://www.crowdway.pl/', '50 EUR', 'N/A', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Crowdway is a crowdfunding platform based in Poland founded in 2015. It operates in the field of equity investment and focuses on supporting startups, small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs), as well as green energy ventures. As the largest crowdinvesting platform in Poland, Crowdway offers extensive information on significant share issues conducted by fast-growing companies and start-ups in the country.\n\nThe platform provides a comprehensive overview of share issues, with a combined value surpassing EUR 20 million, including nearly EUR 9 million in 2021 alone. By showcasing these investment opportunities, Crowdway aims to connect investors with promising ventures in various industries, facilitating the growth and development of the Polish business ecosystem.\n\nTo participate in investments through Crowdway, individuals must meet the minimum investment requirement of 50 EUR. The platform is accessible to investors of legal age, which means anyone 18 years or older can engage with Crowdway.\n\nAlthough the advertised return on investment is not specified, Crowdway provides a trustworthy avenue for individuals looking to invest in startups, SMEs, and green energy projects. With its focus on supporting innovation and sustainability in the Polish market, Crowdway plays a vital role in fostering economic growth and business expansion in the country.\n\nTo learn more about Crowdway and explore investment opportunities, interested individuals can visit their website at https://www.crowdway.pl/.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Every investor who is 18+.', 'crowdway', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(541, 'MICROWD', '/platformLogo/MICROWD.png', '[\"Spain\"]', '[\"Debt\"]', '[\"Personal loans\"]', '2015', 'B-87287108', '[\"Spanish\",\"English\"]', NULL, 'https://www.microwd.es/', '50 EUR', '7%', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'MICROWD is a crowdfunding platform based in Spain that specializes in offering debt-based investment opportunities within the personal loans industry. Established in 2015, the platform aims to support women entrepreneurs in Latin America in launching or enhancing their businesses. MICROWD operates primarily in Spanish and English languages and can be accessed through their website, which is located at https://www.microwd.es/.\n\nInvestors on the MICROWD platform can contribute as little as 50 EUR as a minimum investment. The platform advertises a return rate of 0.07, providing an opportunity for financial gain. However, MICROWD differentiates itself by promoting its dedication to also creating a social impact.\n\nMICROWD welcomes investors from all over the world, allowing them to invest in Euros or US Dollars. This inclusive approach ensures that any citizen can participate and support women entrepreneurs in Latin America.\n\nIn summary, MICROWD is a Spanish crowdfunding platform that focuses on debt-based investments in the personal loans industry. Founded in 2015, the platform\'s website is available in both Spanish and English. With a minimum investment of 50 EUR, investors can expect a return rate of 0.07. MICROWD\'s unique selling point lies in its commitment to empowering women entrepreneurs in Latin America while also offering financial opportunities to its investors, irrespective of their nationality.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Any citizen of the world can invest in Euro and Dólar USD', 'microwd', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(542, 'Enerfip', '/platformLogo/Enerfip.png', '[\"France\"]', '[\"Equity\",\"Debt\"]', '[\"Green energy\"]', '2015', 'ORIAS 15003274', '[\"French\",\"Spanish\"]', NULL, 'https://fr.enerfip.eu/', '10 EUR', '5%', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Enerfip is a crowdfunding platform based in France that was founded in 2015. It focuses on the green energy industry and offers investment opportunities in the form of equity and debt. The platform aims to contribute to the energy transition by empowering citizens and communities to take control of the energy policies in their respective areas. Enerfip achieves this by redirecting savings towards renewable energy projects.\n\nThe platform supports two languages, French and Spanish, making it accessible to investors from multiple countries. The minimum investment required is 10 EUR, allowing individuals with varying budgets to participate. Enerfip advertises a return rate of 0.05, providing potential investors with an indication of the potential profitability of their investments.\n\nEnerfip\'s website, https://fr.enerfip.eu/, serves as a hub for investors to explore and engage with various green energy projects. Through the platform, personal and corporate investors can contribute their funds towards different initiatives in the sector. This not only allows investors to support renewable energy projects but also provides them with an opportunity to make a positive impact on the environment and contribute to the global energy transition.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Personal and corporate', 'enerfip', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56');
