(546, 'Bricksave', '/platformLogo/Bricksave.png', '[\"United Kingdom\"]', '[\"Equity\"]', '[\"Real estate\"]', '2015', '10140737', '[\"English\"]', NULL, 'https://www.bricksave.com/', '1,000 EUR', 'Up to 12%', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Anyone over the age of 18 with a minimum investment of 1,000 EUR can invest in Bricksave. The platform allows individuals to invest in real estate properties globally, providing them with the opportunity to gain higher returns. Bricksave was founded in 2015 and is based in the United Kingdom. The platform offers equity-based investments, allowing investors to become partial owners in institutional-grade properties. \n\nBricksave boasts a user-friendly website available in English, making it accessible to a wide range of investors. The platform aims to make real estate investment hassle-free and low-risk by carefully selecting properties.\n\nInvestors can expect an advertised return of up to 12% on their investments. Bricksave ensures that individuals have direct access to these high-quality real estate investments that were traditionally only available to institutional investors. This creates an opportunity for investors to diversify their portfolios and potentially generate significant returns.\n\nWith its global real estate focus, Bricksave allows investors to choose from a variety of properties in different locations, mitigating the risk associated with investing solely in one market. By enabling individuals to invest in institutional-grade properties with relatively small amounts of capital, Bricksave democratizes real estate investing and provides a pathway for individuals to grow their wealth.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 'bricksave', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(547, 'Bona Fides Invest', '/platformLogo/Bona Fides Invest.png', '[\"Croatia\"]', '[\"Equity\",\"Debt\",\"P2P lending\",\"Reward\",\"Donation\",\"Mini-bonds\"]', '[\"Real estate\",\"Startups\",\"SME\",\"Sustainability\",\"Litigation\",\"Green energy\",\"Health & Science\",\"Logistics\",\"Personal loans\",\"Art\",\"Mortgages\",\"Social cause\",\"Education\",\"Farming\",\"Sport\",\"Maritime\"]', '2014', NULL, '[\"Bulgarian\",\"Croatian\",\"Czech\",\"Danish\",\"English\",\"Finnish\",\"French\",\"German\",\"Greek\",\"Hungarian\",\"Italian\",\"Polish\",\"Portuguese\",\"Romanian\",\"Slovak\",\"Slovenian\",\"Spanish\",\"Swedish\"]', NULL, 'https://bonafidesinvest.eu/', '1 EUR', '4%', 'N/A', '[\"Credit card\",\"Bank transfer\",\"Direct debit\",\"PayPal\",\"Cryptocurrency\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Any individual or organization from around the world can invest through Bona Fides Invest. The platform offers a wide range of investment types including equity, debt, P2P lending, reward-based crowdfunding, donation-based crowdfunding, and mini-bonds. \n\nBona Fides Invest caters to multiple industries, making it suitable for investments in real estate, startups, small and medium enterprises (SMEs), sustainability projects, litigation funding, green energy initiatives, health and science ventures, logistics projects, personal loans, art campaigns, mortgages, social causes, education, farming, sports, and maritime ventures. \n\nEstablished in 2014 and based in Croatia, Bona Fides Invest has a user-friendly website that provides information in multiple languages, including Bulgarian, Croatian, Czech, Danish, English, Finnish, French, German, Greek, Hungarian, Italian, Polish, Portuguese, Romanian, Slovak, Slovenian, Spanish, and Swedish. \n\nWith a minimum investment of just 1 EUR, Bona Fides Invest aims to make crowdfunding accessible to a wide range of investors, from individuals to institutions. The platform offers an advertised return of 0.04.\n\nIn summary, Bona Fides Invest is an E