te, Institutional', 'crowdestate', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(558, 'Fongogo', '/platformLogo/Fongogo.png', '[\"Turkey\"]', '[\"Equity\",\"Reward\",\"Donation\"]', '[\"Startups\",\"SME\",\"Green energy\",\"Health & Science\",\"Logistics\",\"Art\",\"Social cause\",\"Education\",\"Farming\"]', '2013', '3880702760', '[\"Turkish\"]', NULL, 'https://fongogo.com/', '10 EUR', 'N/A', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Fongogo, founded in 2013, is Turkey\'s leading crowdfunding platform that provides digital financing as a service to startups and SMEs. Fongogo offers three types of investments: equity, reward, and donation. This allows a wide range of individuals to invest in various industries such as startups, SMEs, green energy, health & science, logistics, art, social causes, education, and farming. Fongogo aims to support these companies by providing them with the necessary funding to grow and succeed.\n\nThe platform is available in the Turkish language and its website, fongogo.com, serves as the central hub for investors and entrepreneurs. The minimum investment required to participate on Fongogo is 10 EUR, making it accessible to individuals with different financial capacities.\n\nWhile the exact advertised return on investments is not mentioned, Fongogo offers a diverse range of investment options that can cater to different investor preferences. Whether individuals are looking for financial returns, rewards, or simply wish to support a cause, Fongogo provides a platform for them to invest in projects they believe in.\n\nFongogo\'s mission is to facilitate digital financing and democratize the investment landscape, allowing anyone to invest in promising projects. With a focus on startups and SMEs, Fongogo plays a vital role in supporting entrepreneurship and innovation in Turkey.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 'Anyone', 'fongogo', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(559, 'HNW Lending', '/platformLogo/HNW Lending.png', '[\"United Kingdom\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"Real estate\",\"SME\",\"Mortgages\",\"Maritime\"]', '2013', '712956', '[\"English\"]', NULL, 'https://www.hnwlending.co.uk/', '10,000 EUR', '12%', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'HNW Lending is a peer-to-peer (P2P) crowdfunding platform based in the United Kingdom. It specializes in asset-based lending within various industries such as real estate, SMEs, mortgages, and maritime. The platform was founded in 2013 and has been facilitating loans for over eight years.\n\nHNW Lending has established itself as a trusted and reliable platform, having arranged more than 450 loans, totaling over £115 million to date. The company\'s website is available in English, ensuring accessibility for a wider audience.\n\nInvestors on HNW Lending can be individuals, corporates, ISAs (Individual Savings Accounts), or pension funds. The platform allows investors to participate in P2P lending by providing a minimum investment amount of 10,000 EUR.\n\nA key feature that sets HNW Lending apart is the Directors\' first loss position in all loans. This means that the Directors of HNW Lending Ltd bear the initial risk in case of default, providing an added layer of security for investors.\n\nHNW Lending strives to deliver attractive returns to its investors, with an advertised return rate of 0.12. This indicates a potentially profitable investment opportunity for those seeking to diversify their portfolios in the real estate, SME, mortgages, or maritime sectors.\n\nWith its extensive experience, reputable track record, and diverse investment options, HNW Lending offers individuals and organizations the opportunity to participate in P2P lending within the United Kingdom\'s thriving crowdfunding market.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 'Individuals, Corporates, ISAs, Pension funds', 'hnwlending', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
(560, 'fairplaid', '/platformLogo/fairplaid.png', '[\"Germany\"]', '[\"Donation\"]', '[\"Sport\"]', '2013', 'HRB 743209', '[\"German\"]', NULL, 'https://www.fairplaid.org/', '1 EUR', 'N/A', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'fairplaid is a crowdfunding platform based in Germany that specializes in donation-based investments in the sports industry. Founded in 2013, fairplaid allows individuals, teams, and entire clubs to run crowdfunding campaigns to raise funds for various projects. The platform supports projects related to training materials, participation in competitions, advancements, training camps, and more in the field of sports.\n\nThe platform primarily operates in the German language, catering to the local market. With a minimum investment requirement of just 1 EUR, fairplaid aims to make crowdfunding accessible to a wide audience. However, the platform does not advertise any specific return on investment.\n\nUnlike traditional investment crowdfunding platforms, fairplaid focuses solely on facilitating donations for sports-related projects. This makes the platform suitable for personal investors who wish to support athletic endeavors, as well as corporate sponsors looking to contribute to the development of sports teams and athletes.\n\nWith a user-friendly website at https://www.fairplaid.org/, fairplaid offers an intuitive platform for both project creators and investors to connect. Through fairplaid, individuals and organizations can financially support sports projects and help athletes and teams achieve their goals.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Personal, Corporate', 'fairplaid', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
