(562, 'Rebuilding Society', '/platformLogo/Rebuilding Society.png', '[\"United Kingdom\"]', '[\"P2P lending\"]', '[\"SME\"]', '2013', '07885342', '[\"English\"]', NULL, 'https://www.rebuildingsociety.com/', '1,000 GBP', 'N/A', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Rebuilding Society is a crowdfunding platform based in the United Kingdom, specifically designed for peer-to-business lending. The platform was founded in 2013 and focuses on facilitating investments in small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs). \n\nWith English as the primary language, Rebuilding Society provides a user-friendly website through which lenders and borrowers can connect. Their website, found at https://www.rebuildingsociety.com/, offers investors the opportunity to support businesses in need of financing.\n\nOne notable feature of Rebuilding Society is its status as an approved ISA Manager. This means that they provide an Innovative Finance ISA, allowing business owners to utilize their ISA allowance to lend to their own businesses. This feature provides a unique opportunity for personal and corporate investors to support their own ventures while enjoying the benefits of tax-efficient investments.\n\nThe minimum investment required to participate on the Rebuilding Society platform is £1,000 GBP, providing a wide range of investors the opportunity to get involved. Although the platform does not specify the advertised return, investors can expect competitive rates of return through their peer-to-business lending activities.\n\nOverall, Rebuilding Society offers a crowdfunding platform tailored to SMEs in the United Kingdom, with a focus on P2P lending. With its unique ISA feature and user-friendly website, the platform aims to facilitate connections between lenders and borrowers, offering opportunities for growth and support in the business community.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Personal, Corporate', 'rebuildingsociety', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
