(573, 'Verkami', '/platformLogo/Verkami.png', '[\"Andorra\"]', '[\"Donation\"]', '[\"Art\"]', '2010', 'N/A', '[\"English\",\"Galego\",\"Catala\",\"Euskara\",\"Castellano\"]', NULL, 'https://www.verkami.com/', '1 EUR', 'N/A', 'N/A', '[\"N/A\"]', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Verkami is a crowdfunding platform based in Andorra that focuses on the art industry. It was founded in 2010 and is considered one of the pioneers of crowdfunding in Europe. The platform is available in multiple languages, including English, Galego, Catala, Euskara, and Castellano.\n\nVerkami allows individuals and companies to make donations to various art projects. The minimum investment required is 1 EUR, making it accessible to a wide range of investors. However, the platform does not advertise any specific return on investment.\n\nThe founders of Verkami are the Sala family, consisting of a biologist, an art historian, and a doctor. Their shared passion for creativity, art, and knowledge led them to establish the platform in Mataró, Barcelona.\n\nOne of Verkami\'s key strengths is its focus on the art industry. By providing a dedicated platform for artists and art-related projects, it helps connect creators with potential patrons. This allows artists to receive the necessary funding for their projects, while investors can support and engage with the art community.\n\nWhether individuals or corporations, Verkami welcomes a diverse range of investors to contribute to the art projects listed on their platform. Through their website, investors can easily browse available projects and make donations to those that resonate with their interests.\n\nOverall, Verkami provides a unique crowdfunding experience tailored to the art industry, fostering creativity and supporting artists in realizing their visions.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Personal, Corporate', 'verkami', '2023-08-08 09:32:56', '2023-08-08 09:32:56'),
